# Univocity-tools agent rules

Establish context by first reading [AGENTS.md](./AGENTS.md).

## CLIs (apps/)

All tools under `apps/` **must** use **[citty](https://github.com/unjs/citty)**
for argument parsing, help, and nested subcommands. Do not use
`commander`, `yargs`, or manual `process.argv` parsing. See
[docs/agents/cli.md](docs/agents/cli.md).

Each app has **`packages/<app-name>/commoncli.ts`** — use
`define<App>Command` / `with<App>Args` to merge shared flags on every
command and subcommand.

Citty **`run`** handlers must only parse args and call **`run*`** in
**`packages/<app>/main.ts`** — see
[cli-command-structure.mdc](./cli-command-structure.mdc).

## Subprocesses (apps/ and packages/)

All external process invocation in TypeScript under `apps/` and
`packages/` **must** use **`Bun.spawn`**.

Do **not** use Node-compatible APIs (`node:child_process`, `exec`,
`execSync`, `spawn`, `execFile`, etc.) or Bun’s `$` shell helper for
subprocesses. See [docs/agents/subprocess.md](docs/agents/subprocess.md).

## Commits

Use **[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/)** —
title ≤100 characters, body lines ≤72. Full rules:
[commit-conventions.mdc](./.cursor/rules/commit-conventions.mdc).
